RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MYSTIC MALIBU gave chase through the backstretch, closed to the front two deep approaching the eighth pole and was steadily handled to draw off. ICY STARE veered outward leaving the gate then gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn then dug in through the lane to take second the final strides. DEVIN ON EARTH took a quick lead and rated the pace inside, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, gave up the lead nearing the eighth pole then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. DEAREST M. A. was forced outward and into AVALANCHE IS COMIN then picked up the chase, raced near the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. The latter was bumped outward and into AMERICAN DREAMER leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the four path then flattened later yards. AMERICAN DREAMER was bumped outward and into NO SHARING, gave chase through the backstretch, raced in the three path on the turn and showed little in the lane. NO SHARING was bumped at the break and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: Icy Stare
ENTRY.OWNER: Pesaturo Gus and Joy Kevin J
ENTRY.COMMENT: veered out break,chased,rail turn,up 2nd final strides

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 15700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE NOVEMBER 18, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since November 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $ 5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).

CLAIM.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JAMMIN STILL rounded the opening turn about the three path and settled close, challenged leaving the seven sixteenths pole and dueled at mostly even terms, drew clear midway on the far turn and held on under steady encouragement. DUSTWHIRL WONDER settled back off the rail, started a bid approaching the three eighths pole, raced at the rail into the turn but angled to the five path nearing the head of the lane, finished well to take second the final strides and just missed the win. CHESAPEAKE CHARLIE saved ground off the pace, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole and raced in the three path on the far turn, was outfinished in the duel through the stretch then nipped from second the final strides. MY CANDY BIZ stalked toward the inside, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn and flattened inside the eighth pole. REY O REYES stalked the early pace from the three path, closed to the lead leaving the seven sixteenths pole and dueled Jammin Still from that point, but dropped back at the rail midway on the far turn and flattened stride mid-stretch. GOT FLOFFY rated the pace inside, was met past the seven sixteenths pole and gave chase from that point, but dropped back toward the quarter pole and weakened at the rail on the far turn. MAKE WAY rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase into the backstretch but showed little response.

ENTRY.NAME: Got Floffy
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,met 7/16,dueled,weakened rail far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Dustwhirl Wonder
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled off rail,bid 3/8,rail into turn,angled 5p 1/8,up 2nd late

ENTRY.NAME: Jammin Still
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3p 1st turn,challenged 7/16,dueled clear mid turn,held on driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LET'S GO MO saved ground off the pace, bid leaving the three eighths pole and improved at the rail on the far turn, eased out leaving the turn, dug in for the lead later yards and raced clear approaching the wire. LINDA'S TAJ came away a bit awkwardly but took a quick lead while angling to the inside, came under pressure approaching the three eighths pole, drew clear at the rail toward the head of the lane, but was met, and relented in later yards. WAY LUCKY settled off the rail then eased outward into the backstretch, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn and came along for third later yards. WICKED SAUCY raced with the pace two deep, challenged leaving the three eighths pole, raced close through the far turn, was carried out into the lane and flattened stride. SWEET FACTOR settled off the rail, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the stretch. MUNNIS PRETTY rounded the opening turn about the three path, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but weakened into the far turn. AWESOME LUCKYCHARM was never a factor. SUPER SWEETIE raced well back off the rail on the first turn, bore out into the backstretch and was no factor racing wide.

ENTRY.NAME: Let's Go Mo
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid 3/8,rail into turn,up late,clear near wire

ENTRY.NAME: Way Lucky
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,eased out 1/2,chased 7/16,3p far turn,along 3rd late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 93. Allowance Purse 31600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since March 18 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Al lowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OVERLY CRITICAL raced with the pace inside, dueled with the advantage past the three eighths pole, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn, drifted in the upper stretch but dug in when straightened away and raced clear mid-stretch. LATE IN THE GAME saved ground, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and dug in to take second later yards. FREEDOM RIDER settled in the three path the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced at a close disadvantage three wide on the far turn, steadied off the heels of PYEONG CHANG past the eighth pole but dug in to take the nod for third under the wire. The latter raced with the pace two deep, contested at a close disadvantage leaving the three eighths pole, was carried out past the eighth pole finished evenly but was nipped from third under the wire. CANDY INVASION saved ground just off the pace, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and ran evenly down the lane. SANTO settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path, left the turn outside and ran evenly in the stretch. STEAL THE CASH rounded the first turn about the three path, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn and showed little in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Candy Invasion
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased near 3/8,off rail far turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Overly Critical
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace inside,dueled past 3/8,edge rail turn,drifted,held well

ENTRY.NAME: Pyeong Chang
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace,dueled close past 3/8,carried out 1/8,nipped 3rd wire

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 54. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 116 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAST PARTY was bumped inward and into Cruise On By leaving the gate then took over inside and rated the pace, came under pressure toward the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and was steadily handled to hold on well. COMEONTURNMELOOSE saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and dueled through the stretch for second. LIEUTENANT BROWN steadied at the break, raced in the five path the first turn and gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. KING OF LUCK lunged while ducking in leaving the gate then roughed off the heels of Callisto's Brigade into the first turn, picked up the chase past the half mile pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. UNCLE PRESS came in and made contact with Last Party leaving the gate then stalked from the three path, gave chase past the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and flattened in the lane. MOON FALL veered in at the break and settled two deep on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and showed little in the lane. CALLISTO'S BRIGADE was forced in at the break then saved ground close to the early pace, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and weakened in the lane. SCARE DEM was forced in at the break and rounded the first turn about the four path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the five path of the far turn and weakened. CRUISE ON BY mostly saved ground. Per Stewards ruling 112, Last Party is disqualified from earnings.

ENTRY.NAME: King of Luck
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Last Party
ENTRY.OWNER: Don't Chasem Replacem Racing and Armstrong Katina M
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,rated pace,pressured 3/8,rail turn,held well driving

ENTRY.NAME: Callisto's Brigade
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in break,saved ground,chased 3/8,3p far turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Scare Dem
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in break,4p 1st turn,chased 7/16,5p far turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Moon Fall
ENTRY.COMMENT: veered in break,settled 2d,chased 7/16,4p far turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 13100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY MIRACLE MAN took the lead two deep into the first turn and rated the pace, was given rein to keep the edge over Amicalola Falls leaving the three eighths pole, came under pressure past the five sixteenths and drew off under steady handling. CHEERS FOR KITTEN had a brief early lead inside then stalked into the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn, eased out approaching the head of the lane and dug in to take second later yards. SULEMAN saved ground on the first turn, bid past the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn and came along for third later yards. AMICALOLA FALLS raced off the rail on the first turn and stalked into the backstretch, challenged toward the seven sixteenths pole but dropped back through the far turn and flattened stride inside the eighth pole. EARTHQUAKEDIRECTOR came away awkwardly and raced well off the pace and off the rail on the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. SLOE GIN BIZ rounded the opening turn in the three path, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole but flattened at the rail on the far turn. STAVANGER showed little response through the backstretch. Stronger Than Dex became fractious in the gate and was a late scratch.

ENTRY.NAME: Earthquakedirector
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward break,well off pace,off rail,little response

ENTRY.NAME: Suleman
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid past 7/16,3p far turn,along 3rd later yards

ENTRY.NAME: My Miracle Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,kept edge from 3/8,pressured 5/16,drew off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Allowance Purse 30500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 18 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since March 18 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Whe re Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DREAMY SONDE pressured the pace and raced close two deep on the turn, dug in for the nod past the sixteenth pole and held on. SPARKLEINYOUREYE gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn and dueled through the stretch for second. LA MADDALENA stumbled at the break then gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. CAT WITH A NOTION was hustled up and set a pressured pace inside, contested the edge at the rail on the turn, but was met past the sixteenth pole and relented late yards. TRUE FLIRT gave early chase but steadied between horses in the vicinity of the five sixteenths pole, rounded the turn near the rail and ran evenly in the lane. MARINA GRANDE chased outside, rounded the turn about the four path and flattened in the lane. LIVANA chased, raced in the three path on the turn and showed little in the lane. PURE NONSENSE gave chase and raced off the rail on the turn.

ENTRY.OWNER: Rogers Louie and Lewis Jr William R

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 50. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WISHING FOR SPRING gave chase, raced two deep on the turn and dug in through the lane to get up the final yards. BLUE MOUNTAIN was hustled to the lead approaching the three eighths pole and set a pressured pace, contested even terms two deep on the turn, drew clear into the lane but was caught in the final yards. JACKYSINTHECASTLE chased toward the inside, raced at the rail on the turn, angled to the five path into the lane and finished well while gaining on the top two. LET'S DO THIS chased inside, rounded the turn at the rail, eased out leaving the turn then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. I SHALLBE RELEASED gave chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. POWER SONDE came away a bit awkwardly then gave chase, raced in the five path on the turn, left the turn outside and passed rivals. MICHEAUX chased, rounded the turn about the four path and showed little in the lane. VEGAS PRINCESS pressed the pace inside, contested even terms at the rail on the turn then weakened past the eighth pole. A BLONDE THING saved ground. MARLEESBEEBEE had a brief early lead, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but weakened in the six path on the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Vegas Princess
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace inside,even terms rail turn,weakened past 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Wishing for Spring
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,2d turn,dug in lane,up final yards

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Mountain
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled up near 3/8,even terms 2d turn,clear 1/8,caught late
